  "texts": [
    "Additionally, as the tasks of feature extraction and segmentation are not orthogonal, incorrect edge estimation can lead to error propagation.",
    "Therefore, an optional choice is to decouple the original images using traditional image processing methods.",
    "There has already been some work in the fields of object detection and other semantic segmentation domains.",
    "Shan et al. [105] utilized Fourier Transform to derive high and lowfrequency components from images.",
    "These components Figure 3 A comprehensive evaluation is conducted on 23 representative deep-learning models, including U-Net [20], UNet++ [101], SFA [22], PraNet [26], ACSNet [25], MSEG [30], EU-Net [31], SANet [8], MSNet [9], UACANet-S [34], UACANet-L [34], C2FNet [35], DCRNet [53], BDG-Net [50], CaraNet [44], EFA-Net [102], CFA-Net [75], M2SNet [103], Polyp-PVT [33], HSNet [46], DuAT [62], ESFPNet [72], and FeDNet [70], with SAM [104] excluded."
